:<div>

sale /seɪl/

(sales) 

1. N-SING The sale of goods is the act of selling them for money. 销售 

例： Efforts were made to limit the sale of alcohol. 做出努力来限制酒的销售。 

例： ...a proposed arms sale to Saudi Arabia. …拟议中对沙特阿拉伯的武器销售。 

2. N-PLURAL The sales of a product are the quantity of it that is sold. 销售量 

例： The newspaper has sales of 1.72 million. 该报有172万份的销售量。 

例： ...the huge Christmas sales of computer games. …电脑游戏在圣诞节的巨额销售量。 

3. N-PLURAL The part of a company that deals with sales deals with selling the company's products. 销售部门 

例： Until 1983 he worked in sales and marketing. 到1983年为止他一直供职于市场营销部。 

4. N-COUNT A sale is an occasion when a shop sells things at less than their normal price. 减价出售 

例： ...a pair of jeans bought half-price in a sale. …一条减价时半价买的牛仔裤。 

5. N-COUNT A sale is an event when goods are sold to the person who offers the highest price. 拍卖 

例： The Old Master was bought by dealers at the Christie's sale. 这幅早期名画被商人们在克里斯蒂的拍卖会上买走。 

6. PHRASE If something is for sale , it is being offered to people to buy. 供出售 

例： The yacht is for sale at a price of 1.7 million dollars. 这艘游艇以170万美元的价格待售。 

7. PHRASE If products in a shop are on sale , they can be bought for less than their normal price. 减价出售 

例： A good shopper doesn't just buy things because they're on sale. 善于购物的人不会仅仅因为商品减价出售就买。 

8. PHRASE Products that are on sale can be bought. 出售 

例： English textbooks and dictionaries are on sale everywhere. 英语教材和词典到处都有出售。 

例： Tickets go on sale this week. 票本周开始出售。 

9. PHRASE If a property or company is up for sale , its owner is trying to sell it. 待售 

例： The mansion has been put up for sale. 该豪宅已待售。

